" ============================================================================
" Meow-style selection-first editing (mirrors the Emacs init.el meow QWERTY)
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" The meow model (Kakoune-like): SELECT first, then ACT.
"   * selecting motions (w W e E b B f t x) enter Visual with a selection
"   * H J K L extend the selection; h j k l collapse it and move
"   * action keys work on the selection, or on the char under the cursor:
"       s = kill/cut   d = delete (black hole)   c = change
"       y = copy       p = paste                 r = replace with clipboard
"   * there are therefore NO d/c/y operators: no dd, cw, diw, yy.
"     to act on a whole line: x (select line) then s / d / c / y.
" This follows init.el's meow keys, not vanilla Vim: q quits, m joins, g
" cancels the selection, v / n / N drive search, , / . grab the inner / bounds
" of a thing, ' repeats, and u / U are the IDE's undo / redo (shared with the
" Emacs C-/ stack). Emacs chords (C-a/e/k/y/w/d, C-x..., C-s, C-space, M-x)
" still work everywhere — they are routed to the IDE up top.

" --- lowercase h j k l: move, dropping the selection ---
xnoremap h <Esc>h
xnoremap j <Esc>j
xnoremap k <Esc>k
xnoremap l <Esc>l

" --- uppercase H J K L: start / extend a selection ---
nnoremap H vh
nnoremap J vj
nnoremap K vk
nnoremap L vl
xnoremap H h
xnoremap J j
xnoremap K k
xnoremap L l

" --- selecting motions: enter Visual with a selection ---
" word / WORD under the cursor
nnoremap w viw
xnoremap w <Esc>viw
nnoremap W viW
xnoremap W <Esc>viW
" e / E: select to the end of the next word / WORD. In Visual, GROW the
" selection rightward a word at a time, keeping the left end anchored
" (re-anchored from the `< / `> marks so it works first press and repeats).
nnoremap e eviw
xnoremap e <Esc>`>ev`<
nnoremap E EviW
xnoremap E <Esc>`>Ev`<
" b / B: select back a word / WORD. In Visual, GROW leftward a word at a
" time, keeping the right end anchored.
nnoremap b bviwo
xnoremap b <Esc>`<bv`>
nnoremap B BviWo
xnoremap B <Esc>`<Bv`>
" find / till a character (selects up to it)
nnoremap f vf
nnoremap t vt
nnoremap F vF
nnoremap T vT
" whole line; tap x again to grow the selection down a line
nnoremap x V
xnoremap x j
nnoremap X G
xnoremap X G
" expand / shrink the selection by syntax (meow-block / meow-to-block)
nnoremap o <action>(EditorSelectWord)
xnoremap o <action>(EditorSelectWord)
nnoremap O <action>(EditorUnSelectWord)
xnoremap O <action>(EditorUnSelectWord)
" reverse the selection (swap its active end)
xnoremap ; o
" inner / bounds of a thing: , or . then a text-object char, e.g. ,( or .(
nnoremap , vi
nnoremap . va
" ' repeats the last change (meow keeps . for bounds, above)
nnoremap ' .
" cancel the selection (meow-cancel-selection)
nnoremap g <Esc>
xnoremap g <Esc>
" join lines (meow-join)
nnoremap m J
xnoremap m J
" quit the editor (meow-quit)
nnoremap q :q<cr>
" visit: open the IDE search; n / N then walk the matches (meow-visit)
nnoremap v <action>(Find)

" --- insert around the selection / open lines ---
" I / A open a line above / below (meow-open-above / meow-open-below)
nnoremap I O
nnoremap A o
" in Visual, i / a drop in at the start / end of the selection
xnoremap i <Esc>`<i
xnoremap a <Esc>`>a
xnoremap I <Esc>O
xnoremap A <Esc>o

" --- act on the selection (or the char under the cursor) ---
" kill / cut to the clipboard
nnoremap s x
xnoremap s d
" delete without touching the clipboard (black hole register)
nnoremap d "_x
nnoremap D "_X
xnoremap d "_d
xnoremap D "_d
" change
nnoremap c cl
" copy
nnoremap y yl
" replace the selection with the clipboard, leaving the clipboard intact
xnoremap r "_dP
" redo on U; u stays IdeaVim's native undo. Both already run on the IDE's
" UndoManager (the same stack as Emacs C-/), so DON'T use <action>($Undo/$Redo)
" here — those fire with no editor in their data context and silently no-op.
nnoremap U <C-r>